# ChEMBLdb download instructions

Main requirement: install lftp on your system (preferred for reliable recursive downloads).

Install lftp:
- macOS (Homebrew):
  brew install lftp
- Ubuntu/Debian:
  sudo apt install lftp
- Fedora/RHEL:
  sudo dnf install lftp

Install sqlite (for local querying):
- macOS (Homebrew):
  brew install sqlite
- Ubuntu/Debian:
  sudo apt install sqlite3
- Fedora/RHEL:
  sudo dnf install sqlite

Download ChEMBLdb (latest release) with lftp:
  cd database
  lftp -e "set ssl:verify-certificate no; mirror --verbose --parallel=4 --continue --only-newer /pub/databases/chembl/ChEMBLdb/latest latest; bye" https://ftp.ebi.ac.uk

Notes:
- This mirrors the entire latest/ directory from the EBI FTP site into database/latest/.
- Adjust --parallel if your connection is slower/faster.

Fallback (wget recursive):
  cd database
  wget -r -N -np -nH --cut-dirs=4 -e robots=off \
    https://ftp.ebi.ac.uk/pub/databases/chembl/ChEMBLdb/latest/

Notes on wget:
- This will create database/latest/ and download the full tree.
- Use --continue if you need to resume large downloads.

Extract the SQLite database after download:
  cd database
  tar -xzf latest/chembl_*_sqlite.tar.gz -C latest

If the SQLite file is gzipped, unpack it:
  gunzip latest/chembl_*_sqlite/*.db.gz

Expected SQLite DB path (used by this repo):
  database/latest/chembl_<VERSION>/chembl_<VERSION>_sqlite/chembl_<VERSION>.db

Example (ChEMBL 36):
  database/latest/chembl_36/chembl_36_sqlite/chembl_36.db
